    "body": "A simple example how to calculate layernorm forward in 2 stages using `QuACK`.\r\n\r\nPerformance on `H100`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTensor dimensions: [32768, 32768]\r\nInput and Output Data type: BFloat16\r\nInput tensor shapes:\r\nx: torch.Size([32768, 32768]), dtype: torch.bfloat16\r\nw: torch.Size([32768]), dtype: torch.float32\r\nExecuting kernel...\r\nKernel execution time: 1.4376 ms\r\nMem throughput: 2987.56 GB/s\r\nRef kernel execution time: 1.8226 ms\r\nRef mem throughput: 2356.48 GB/s\r\n```",
